  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C).",
    "2. Tear the French bread into 1-inch cubes and place in a 9x13-inch baking dish.",
    "3. In a separate bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt.",
    "4. Pour the egg mixture over the bread cubes and let sit for 5 minutes.",
    "5. Sprinkle the chewy on top of the bread mixture.",
    "6. Dot the top with butter.",
    "7. Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until golden brown.",
    "8. Serve warm."
